'I' (named i , plural ies)Brown & Kiddle (1870) The institutes of English grammar, p. 19.
Ies is the plural of the English name of the letter; the plural of the letter itself is rendered I's, Is, i's, or is. is the ninth letter and a vowel in the ISO basic Latin alphabet.
